<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-20] The test results XML produced by surefire doesn&apos;t escape quotes properly, resulting in invalid XML</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-20</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When surefire runs junit tests, as part of it&apos;s XML output, it takes your java system properties and creates a properties element. If Any of the properties have quotes in them, they are not escaped. For example (file attached as well):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;testsuite errors=&quot;0&quot; tests=&quot;9&quot; time=&quot;2.972&quot; failures=&quot;0&quot; name=&quot;ca.ucalgary.commons.pmgt.ModelTest&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;properties&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property value=&quot;Java(TM) 2 Runtime Environment, Standard Edition&quot; name=&quot;java.runtime.name&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property value=&quot;/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/1.4.2/Libraries&quot; name=&quot;sun.boot.library.path&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property value=&quot;1.4.2-54&quot; name=&quot;java.vm.version&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property value=&quot;true&quot; name=&quot;awt.nativeDoubleBuffering&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property value=&quot;false&quot; name=&quot;gopherProxySet&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property value=&quot;&quot;Apple Computer, Inc.&quot;&quot; name=&quot;java.vm.vendor&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property value=&quot;http://apple.com/&quot; name=&quot;java.vendor.url&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note the value of java.vm.vendor is &quot;Apple Computer, Inc&quot;, including the quotes. They should be replaces with their entity (&amp;quot;) equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The surefire report plugin subsequently errors on validatiion of this file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;J&lt;/p&gt;</description>
